com.volvo.softproduct.canparser

Class SignalDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.volvo.softproduct.canparser.SignalDefinition

  • public class SignalDefinition
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to describe the signal received in a CAN frame message. Definition of a signal is: "a part of the 64 bit data value that can be interprented as a presentable value" Note! There can be several signals in one CAN Frame message (each signal on different bits in the 64 bits data value)

      • SignalDefinition

        public SignalDefinition(int canId,
                int startBit,
                int numberOfDataBits,
                java.util.List<SignalScale> scaleValues,
                SignalType outputType,
                java.lang.String unit,
                java.lang.String signalDescription)
        Constructor SignalDefinition()
        Parameters:
        canId - ID of the CAN Frame
        startBit - Start bit of the signal (counter from least significant bit)
        numberOfDataBits - Number of bit the signal occupies (counted from the startBit)
        scaleValues - A list of mathematical operations used to scale the received signal from Integers to presentation values.
        outputType - A flag that indicates if the return value should be DOUBLE, LONG or a FLAG.
        unit - Unit of the signal (e.g m/s)
        signalDescription - Description of the signal
